#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-overview.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "&deng; Overview"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-overview.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &deng; is a lightweight virtualization solution to run multiple virtual Linux environments (containers) simultaneously on top of a single Linux kernel, without a hypervisor. Containers are isolated using Kernel cgroups ( <xref linkend=\"vle-docker-cgroup\"/> ) and <xref linkend=\"vle-docker-namespace\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-overview.xml:19
#, no-c-format
msgid "Full virtualization solutions, such as &xen;, &kvm;, or &libvirt;, are based on simulating a complete hardware environment and running multiple operating system instances inside these virtual machines. The &deng; provides operating-system-level virtualization: a single Linux kernel controls multiple isolated containers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-overview.xml:26
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &deng; allows developers and system administrators to manage the complete life cycle of images. The &deng; makes it easy to build, ship, and run images containing applications."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-overview.xml:31
#, no-c-format
msgid "&deng; has the following advantages:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-overview.xml:36
#, no-c-format
msgid "Isolation of applications through containers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-overview.xml:41
#, no-c-format
msgid "Near-native performance, as the &deng; manages allocation of resources in real time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-overview.xml:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "Control network interfaces and resources available inside containers through cgroups."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-overview.xml:53
#, no-c-format
msgid "Versioning of images."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-overview.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "Building new images based on existing ones."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-overview.xml:63
#, no-c-format
msgid "Container orchestration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-overview.xml:68
#, no-c-format
msgid "&deng; has the following limitations:"
msgstr ""

